    <h1>Mexico</h1>
    <div class="ruler"></div>
    <h3>Food</h3>
    <p><img src="/arthur/i/games/connectworld/food_mex.gif" alt="Illustration of tamale" width="101" height="68" class="float-right cw-img">A tamale is a little meat or vegetable pie made in a cornmeal dough called masa. The tamale is wrapped in a dry corn husk and steamed until cooked. The corn husk is not eaten.</p>
    <div class="ruler"></div>
    <h3>Music</h3>
    <p><img src="/arthur/i/games/connectworld/music_mex.gif" alt="Illustration of a maracas" width="101" height="68" class="float-right cw-img">Maracas are percussion instruments. They were originally made from gourds partially filled with seeds or dried beans. Nowadays they may be wood or plastic. Maracas are played by shaking them.</p>
    <div class="ruler"></div>
    <h3>Sport</h3>
    <p><img src="/arthur/i/games/connectworld/sport_mex.gif" alt="Illustration of a soccer ball" width="101" height="68" class="float-right cw-img"> Soccer is the most popular sport in the world. As of 2003, Mexico alone has 20 teams. Two teams try to get a ball through their opponent's goal without using their arms or hands. All other parts of the body are allowed. Goalies may use their hands.</p>
    <div class="ruler"></div>
    <h3>Flag</h3>
    <p><img src="/arthur/i/games/connectworld/flag_mex.gif" alt="The Mexican flag" width="101" height="68" class="float-right cw-img"> The Mexican flag is green on the left, white in the middle, and red on the right. In the middle is a picture of an eagle standing on a cactus and eating a snake. This emblem recalls an Aztec legend of how Mexico City was founded.</p>
